cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.GR

The paper focuses on deep learning for computer vision, specifically on unsupervised domain adaptation for semantic segmentation using simulated data. This falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also utilizes generative adversarial networks (GANs) for the adaptation, which is a popular technique in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the use of simulators and depth information relates to robotics (cs.RO) and graphics (cs.GR) sub-categories.
